<font color="#FF0000">KEEP IT SIMPLE, STUPID!</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jan  7 15:56:21 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Recently, there has been a great deal of lofty logic, academic posturing and moot revelation regarding the Viet Nam war.  The Viet Nam war started, was fought, and ended for the same assorted reasons every war has been fought.  To keep it simple..it is prudent to acknowledge that there were many reasons... religious, political, economic, racial, etc.<br><br>
Large masses of people do not communicate with large masses of people.. communication occurs between the masses through individuals or small groups of people, selected or self appointed through power acquired by physical force, proclaimed divinity, royalty, prevarication or any other means a gullible populace will fall for. <br><br>
The consequences of war are always the same... great profit is made for a few... a great price is paid by many.  It is tangibly obvious in the visible death and destruction and more fleeting vague in the hearts of the survivors.<br><br>
Always there are advances in technology, strategies, and tactics.  War, the most serious proponent of necessity, is essentially the most ardent mother of invention.  Always there are lessons learned.  Legions of historians wet their pens to record fact and fiction, to hide or reveal.  Usually, the lessons are ignored or forgotten.<br><br>
Consistently, some cowards are proclaimed as heroes and many genuine heroes go unrecognized.  Those who faced the greatest horror in some role of protection are quickly forgotten by the protected.  Cowardly dissidents, religious fanatics and greedy economic opportunist labor to dismantle patriotic themes to hide their parasitic actions during and after the military  contests. The feast of freedom proffered by the efforts of the sacrificers is always visited by the freeloaders who are more inclined to criticize the chef.... certainly, they don't hang around to do the dishes!<br><br>
Never will logic, wisdom, love or a kind word thwart the aggressor and the fanatic.  Immorality and erosion of ethic will not respond to legislation of any rule or law that is not enforced or enforceable.<br><br>
I am not unaware of Henry Steele Commanger's warning that those who do not know history are destined to relive it.. but I have news for everyone...you're going to relive it anyway!<br><br>
In summary,&quot;Keep it simple, Stupid!&quot; suggests that while I lend an ear to what happened...I prefer to bend my back to tend to the victims and survivors. Constant proclamations of the faults of the United States of America seem to remind me of the freeloaders who chastise the chef.<br><br>
Mustang Two Four<br><br>
P.S.  Would anyone like to address the lingering turmoil in the lives of American patriots who served in Viet Nam..PTSD?
